Computation of Specific area and Plotting The Coordinates

estimate_area.Rd

Provide an approximation of the area of a Shape by using Monte Carlo Approach, with the function estimate_area(), we can simulate coordinates of x and y , which are uniformly distributed between 0 and 1 according to the number that we write in the function. At the end, we have an approximate area calculated by counting the number of points inside the shape divided by the total number of points.

estimate_area(B = 5000, seed = 10)

Arguments

B

A numeric (integer) used to denote the number of coordinates for simulation.
seed

A numeric used to control the seed of the random number generator used by this function.

Value

A list containing the following attributes:

Estimated_area

Estimated area of a shape

points

Coordinates of simulated points

Author

Özgür Aydemir, Sophie La Gennusa, Louis del Perugia, Daniel Szenes, Francesca Darino

Examples

estimate_area(B = 500, seed = 100)
